description: In a world where all superheros have either been destroyed or forced into hiding by the Criminal Underworld a few remaining heroes don the costumes of many different heroes to rally against the Underworld.

Tales of terror and suspense from this pre-code 1950's classic title!

Harvey Horrors originally published 26 issues of the Chamber Of Chills in the 1950s. Now for the first time they have been collected together in this exclusive 4 volume set. Each volume contains between 6 7 complete issues reprinted for the very first time as a complete collection. This volume is a full-color collection of June-December 1951, issues 21-24, and February-April 1952, issues 5-7.

Featuring a special introduction from Joe Hill and illustration by Glenn Chadbourne and profiles of some of the genres leading artists, such as Al Avison, Lee Elias, Bob Powell and Vic Donahue, plus examples of their original artwork.

volume.name: Harvey Horrors Collected Works: Chamber of Chills
